<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/456232-did-anyone-else-find-it-hard-to-believe">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Did anyone else find it hard to believe the conditions were as nice as they were in silo 17? The electricity is still running, plants are still growing (&amp; dying), no one runs into one another even after 34 YEARS (?!), the bodies are still heavy bodies and not skeletons, the generator/pump under the water is almost perfectly preserved, no obvious signs of decay, rust, or disrepair. Is this a little too unbelievable? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
