    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1437816181" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1437816181" />
    <a title="Dem" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2752994-dem"><img alt="Dem" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552868566p2/2752994.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1437816181?book_show_action=true">Nov 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dem" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dem" href="/user/show/2752994-dem">Dem</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Dem by: </span>
      Book club read 
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2752994-dem?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2752994-dem?shelf=bookclub-reads">bookclub-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1437816181" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13753984032469841665">I enjoy Post apocalyptic Stories every now and again and as this book had been getting rave reviews I had to give it a go. <br/><br/>The idea is really interesting,<i> &quot;This is the story of mankind clawing for survival, of mankind on the edge. The world outside has grown unkind, the view of it limited, talk of it forbidden. But there are always those who hope, who dream. These are the dangerous people, the residents who infect others with their optimism. Their punishment is simple. They are given the very th</i></span>
  <span id="freeText13753984032469841665" style="display:none">I enjoy Post apocalyptic Stories every now and again and as this book had been getting rave reviews I had to give it a go. <br /><br />The idea is really interesting,<i> "This is the story of mankind clawing for survival, of mankind on the edge. The world outside has grown unkind, the view of it limited, talk of it forbidden. But there are always those who hope, who dream. These are the dangerous people, the residents who infect others with their optimism. Their punishment is simple. They are given the very thing they profess to want: They are allowed outside"</i><br /><br />The first chapter had me gripped and I really thought I had another <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6288.The_Road" title="The Road by Cormac McCarthy" rel="nofollow noopener">The Road</a> in my hands and really looked forward to something special. <br />While I did like the concept of the novel I found the book lost its initial impact after the first couple of chapters. I found the characters very weak and poorly developed and the I got bogged down in the overwhelming descriptions of everything and this made the book seem endless. There are a couple of twists and turns towards the end of the novel but they came too late for me.<br /><br />Having read and loved <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6288.The_Road" title="The Road by Cormac McCarthy" rel="nofollow noopener">The Road</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6690798.The_Passage__The_Passage___1_" title="The Passage (The Passage, #1) by Justin Cronin" rel="nofollow noopener">The Passage</a> I was hoping that Wool would be just as atmospheric and eerie but unfortunately it didn't appeal to me.<br /><br />The book is over 550 pages long and I really felt that it could have been a lot shorter .<br /><br />Having read this back in November, I had to re-read this one for a book club read this month. I listened to it this time and the narrator was quite good but the book dragged regardless.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13753984032469841665" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


