<span id="freeTextContainer16562288060241550037">This reminded me of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/307791.The_City_of_Ember__Book_of_Ember___1_' title='The City of Ember (Book of Ember, #1) by Jeanne DuPrau' rel='nofollow noopener'> The City of Ember</a> and a lot of other similar shows and books. I think IT and Engineering would be evenly matched adversaries for power in the silos. Even if they cycled with a history as often as the moties, control over the energy, food, and water should balance out any control that IT had.<br/><br/>That being said I really like Juliette.</span>
  <span id="freeText16562288060241550037" style="display:none">This reminded me of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/307791.The_City_of_Ember__Book_of_Ember___1_" title="The City of Ember (Book of Ember, #1) by Jeanne DuPrau" rel="nofollow noopener"> The City of Ember</a> and a lot of other similar shows and books. I think IT and Engineering would be evenly matched adversaries for power in the silos. Even if they cycled with a history as often as the moties, control over the energy, food, and water should balance out any control that IT had.<br /><br />That being said I really like Juliette.</span>
